pull_request.body:
[![Mend Renovate](https://app.renovatebot.com/images/banner.svg)](https://renovatebot.com)

This PR contains the following updates:

| Package | Update | Change |
|---|---|---|
| [dev.zio:zio](https://zio.dev) ([source](https://togithub.com/zio/zio)) | patch | `2.0.2` -> `2.0.3` |

---

### Release Notes

<details>
<summary>zio/zio</summary>

### [`v2.0.3`](https://togithub.com/zio/zio/releases/tag/v2.0.3)

[Compare Source](https://togithub.com/zio/zio/compare/v2.0.2...v2.0.3)

This release contains a variety of optimizations and bug fixes. In particular asynchronous operations in the runtime are significantly faster based on work by [@​jdegoes](https://togithub.com/jdegoes). As always, thanks for using ZIO and we're so excited to see everything that you are building with ZIO!

##### Performance Improvements

The performance of many core operations, including interruptible async operations and joining fibers, have been greatly improved, by a combination of micro-optimization and interning. A new "gen 3" optimization allows the ZIO 2 runtime system to avoid stack unwinding for fast asynchronous operations, and work stealing enables one run loop suspended by an async operation to steal a bit of work on behalf of another fiber. The weak concurrent bag for root fibers has been completely re-written with massive performance improvements in forkDaemon-heavy scenarios. Overall, these performance improvements make the ZIO 2 runtime system faster than it's ever been.

Future areas of improvement include additional micro-optimizations in the runtime system, lower overhead for the fiber actor machinery, and intelligent auto-tuning for JVM stack or reified stack run modes.

</details>

### Release Notes

<details>
<summary>spring-projects/spring-framework</summary>

### [`v6.0.0-RC3`](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/releases/tag/v6.0.0-RC3)

[Compare Source](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/compare/v6.0.0-RC2...v6.0.0-RC3)

##### :star: New Features

-   Support `@RequestPart` arguments for `@HttpExchange` methods [#​29420](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29420)
-   Processing of charset in Content-Type Header not case-insensitive [#​29416](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29416)
-   Allow for external customization and i8n of the "title" of an RFC 7807 response [#​29407](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29407)
-   Automatically register directories for registered resource hints [#​29403](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29403)
-   Allow registration of resource hint for root directory [#​29402](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29402)
-   Load `ApplicationContextFailureProcessor` implementations from `spring.factories` [#​29387](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29387)
-   Simplify mapping of custom exception to an RFC 7807 response in ResponseEntityExceptionHandler [#​29384](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29384)
-   Introduce SimpleValueStyler for use with ToStringCreator [#​29381](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29381)
-   Make DefaultValueStyler extensible [#​29380](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29380)
-   Introduce DataFieldMaxValueIncrementer for MariaDB [#​29379](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/pull/29379)
-   Handle case where `ResponseEntity` and `ProblemDetail` don't agree on the HTTP status to use [#​29378](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29378)
-   Provide AOT support for `HttpServiceProxyFactory` clients [#​29271](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29271)
-   Revise logging in the TestContext framework [#​29229](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29229)

##### :lady_beetle: Bug Fixes

-   Align server observation contextual names with OTel semantic conventions  [#​29424](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29424)

-   AOT processing loses bean aliases [#​29391](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29391)
-   WebClient and WebFlux Observation do not propagate context [#​29388](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/pull/29388)
-   HttpServiceProxyFactory raises IllegalStateException if created through the builder and declared as a bean [#​29376](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29376)
-   Multiple `@ImportRuntimeHints` in the type hierarchy should be supported [#​29361](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29361)

-   Introduce DataFieldMaxValueIncrementer for MariaDB [#​29379](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/pull/29379)
-   Handle case where `ResponseEntity` and `ProblemDetail` don't agree on the HTTP status to use [#​29378](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29378)
-   Provide AOT support for `HttpServiceProxyFactory` clients [#​29271](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29271)

pull_request.body:
[![Mend Renovate](https://app.renovatebot.com/images/banner.svg)](https://renovatebot.com)

This PR contains the following updates:

| Package | Update | Change |
|---|---|---|
| [dev.zio:zio](https://zio.dev) ([source](https://togithub.com/zio/zio)) | patch | `2.0.2` -> `2.0.3` |

---

### Release Notes

<details>
<summary>zio/zio</summary>

### [`v2.0.3`](https://togithub.com/zio/zio/releases/tag/v2.0.3)

[Compare Source](https://togithub.com/zio/zio/compare/v2.0.2...v2.0.3)

This release contains a variety of optimizations and bug fixes. In particular asynchronous operations in the runtime are significantly faster based on work by [@​jdegoes](https://togithub.com/jdegoes). As always, thanks for using ZIO and we're so excited to see everything that you are building with ZIO!

##### Performance Improvements

The performance of many core operations, including interruptible async operations and joining fibers, have been greatly improved, by a combination of micro-optimization and interning. A new "gen 3" optimization allows the ZIO 2 runtime system to avoid stack unwinding for fast asynchronous operations, and work stealing enables one run loop suspended by an async operation to steal a bit of work on behalf of another fiber. The weak concurrent bag for root fibers has been completely re-written with massive performance improvements in forkDaemon-heavy scenarios. Overall, these performance improvements make the ZIO 2 runtime system faster than it's ever been.

Future areas of improvement include additional micro-optimizations in the runtime system, lower overhead for the fiber actor machinery, and intelligent auto-tuning for JVM stack or reified stack run modes.

</details>

### Release Notes

<details>
<summary>spring-projects/spring-framework</summary>

### [`v6.0.0-RC3`](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/releases/tag/v6.0.0-RC3)

[Compare Source](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/compare/v6.0.0-RC2...v6.0.0-RC3)

##### :star: New Features

-   Support `@RequestPart` arguments for `@HttpExchange` methods [#​29420](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29420)
-   Processing of charset in Content-Type Header not case-insensitive [#​29416](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29416)
-   Allow for external customization and i8n of the "title" of an RFC 7807 response [#​29407](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29407)
-   Automatically register directories for registered resource hints [#​29403](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29403)
-   Allow registration of resource hint for root directory [#​29402](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29402)
-   Load `ApplicationContextFailureProcessor` implementations from `spring.factories` [#​29387](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29387)
-   Simplify mapping of custom exception to an RFC 7807 response in ResponseEntityExceptionHandler [#​29384](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29384)
-   Introduce SimpleValueStyler for use with ToStringCreator [#​29381](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29381)
-   Make DefaultValueStyler extensible [#​29380](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29380)
-   Introduce DataFieldMaxValueIncrementer for MariaDB [#​29379](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/pull/29379)
-   Handle case where `ResponseEntity` and `ProblemDetail` don't agree on the HTTP status to use [#​29378](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29378)
-   Provide AOT support for `HttpServiceProxyFactory` clients [#​29271](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29271)
-   Revise logging in the TestContext framework [#​29229](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29229)

##### :lady_beetle: Bug Fixes

-   Align server observation contextual names with OTel semantic conventions  [#​29424](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29424)
-   Matching path pattern is not set in reactive ServerRequestObservationContext [#​29422](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29422)
-   PartEvent upload fails with JdkClientHttpConnector [#​29400](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29400)
-   Native image FileSystem should not be closed after classpath scanning [#​29397](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29397)
-   AOT processing loses bean aliases [#​29391](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29391)
-   WebClient and WebFlux Observation do not propagate context [#​29388](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/pull/29388)
-   HttpServiceProxyFactory raises IllegalStateException if created through the builder and declared as a bean [#​29376](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29376)
-   Multiple `@ImportRuntimeHints` in the type hierarchy should be supported [#​29361](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29361)

##### :hammer: Dependency Upgrades

-   Upgrade to Jackson 2.14.0-rc3 [#​29405](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29405)

##### :heart: Contributors

Thank you to all the contributors who worked on this release:

[@​fmbenhassine](https://togithub.com/fmbenhassine), [@​imkulwant](https://togithub.com/imkulwant), [@​izeye](https://togithub.com/izeye), and [@​marcingrzejszczak](https://togithub.com/marcingrzejszczak)

</details>

### Release Notes

<details>
<summary>spring-projects/spring-framework</summary>

### [`v6.0.0-RC3`](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/releases/tag/v6.0.0-RC3)

[Compare Source](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/compare/v6.0.0-RC2...v6.0.0-RC3)

##### :star: New Features

-   Support `@RequestPart` arguments for `@HttpExchange` methods [#​29420](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29420)
-   Processing of charset in Content-Type Header not case-insensitive [#​29416](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29416)
-   Allow for external customization and i8n of the "title" of an RFC 7807 response [#​29407](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29407)
-   Automatically register directories for registered resource hints [#​29403](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29403)
-   Allow registration of resource hint for root directory [#​29402](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29402)
-   Load `ApplicationContextFailureProcessor` implementations from `spring.factories` [#​29387](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29387)
-   Simplify mapping of custom exception to an RFC 7807 response in ResponseEntityExceptionHandler [#​29384](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29384)
-   Introduce SimpleValueStyler for use with ToStringCreator [#​29381](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29381)
-   Make DefaultValueStyler extensible [#​29380](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29380)
-   Introduce DataFieldMaxValueIncrementer for MariaDB [#​29379](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/pull/29379)
-   Handle case where `ResponseEntity` and `ProblemDetail` don't agree on the HTTP status to use [#​29378](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29378)
-   Provide AOT support for `HttpServiceProxyFactory` clients [#​29271](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29271)
-   Revise logging in the TestContext framework [#​29229](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29229)

##### :lady_beetle: Bug Fixes

-   Align server observation contextual names with OTel semantic conventions  [#​29424](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29424)
-   Matching path pattern is not set in reactive ServerRequestObservationContext [#​29422](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29422)
-   PartEvent upload fails with JdkClientHttpConnector [#​29400](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29400)
-   Native image FileSystem should not be closed after classpath scanning [#​29397](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29397)
-   AOT processing loses bean aliases [#​29391](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29391)
-   WebClient and WebFlux Observation do not propagate context [#​29388](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/pull/29388)
-   HttpServiceProxyFactory raises IllegalStateException if created through the builder and declared as a bean [#​29376](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29376)
-   Multiple `@ImportRuntimeHints` in the type hierarchy should be supported [#​29361](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29361)

##### :hammer: Dependency Upgrades

-   Upgrade to Jackson 2.14.0-rc3 [#​29405](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29405)

##### :heart: Contributors

Thank you to all the contributors who worked on this release:

[@​fmbenhassine](https://togithub.com/fmbenhassine), [@​imkulwant](https://togithub.com/imkulwant), [@​izeye](https://togithub.com/izeye), and [@​marcingrzejszczak](https://togithub.com/marcingrzejszczak)

</details>

This PR contains the following updates:

---

### Release Notes

<details>
<summary>zio/zio</summary>

### [`v2.0.3`](https://togithub.com/zio/zio/releases/tag/v2.0.3)

[Compare Source](https://togithub.com/zio/zio/compare/v2.0.2...v2.0.3)

This release contains a variety of optimizations and bug fixes. In particular asynchronous operations in the runtime are significantly faster based on work by [@​jdegoes](https://togithub.com/jdegoes). As always, thanks for using ZIO and we're so excited to see everything that you are building with ZIO!

##### Performance Improvements

The performance of many core operations, including interruptible async operations and joining fibers, have been greatly improved, by a combination of micro-optimization and interning. A new "gen 3" optimization allows the ZIO 2 runtime system to avoid stack unwinding for fast asynchronous operations, and work stealing enables one run loop suspended by an async operation to steal a bit of work on behalf of another fiber. The weak concurrent bag for root fibers has been completely re-written with massive performance improvements in forkDaemon-heavy scenarios. Overall, these performance improvements make the ZIO 2 runtime system faster than it's ever been.

Future areas of improvement include additional micro-optimizations in the runtime system, lower overhead for the fiber actor machinery, and intelligent auto-tuning for JVM stack or reified stack run modes.

</details>

### Release Notes

<details>
<summary>spring-projects/spring-framework</summary>

### [`v6.0.0-RC3`](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/releases/tag/v6.0.0-RC3)

[Compare Source](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/compare/v6.0.0-RC2...v6.0.0-RC3)

##### :star: New Features

-   Support `@RequestPart` arguments for `@HttpExchange` methods [#​29420](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29420)
-   Processing of charset in Content-Type Header not case-insensitive [#​29416](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29416)
-   Allow for external customization and i8n of the "title" of an RFC 7807 response [#​29407](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29407)
-   Automatically register directories for registered resource hints [#​29403](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29403)
-   Allow registration of resource hint for root directory [#​29402](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29402)
-   Load `ApplicationContextFailureProcessor` implementations from `spring.factories` [#​29387](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29387)
-   Simplify mapping of custom exception to an RFC 7807 response in ResponseEntityExceptionHandler [#​29384](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29384)
-   Introduce SimpleValueStyler for use with ToStringCreator [#​29381](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29381)
-   Make DefaultValueStyler extensible [#​29380](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29380)
-   Introduce DataFieldMaxValueIncrementer for MariaDB [#​29379](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/pull/29379)
-   Handle case where `ResponseEntity` and `ProblemDetail` don't agree on the HTTP status to use [#​29378](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29378)
-   Provide AOT support for `HttpServiceProxyFactory` clients [#​29271](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29271)
-   Revise logging in the TestContext framework [#​29229](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29229)

##### :lady_beetle: Bug Fixes

-   Align server observation contextual names with OTel semantic conventions  [#​29424](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29424)
-   Matching path pattern is not set in reactive ServerRequestObservationContext [#​29422](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29422)
-   PartEvent upload fails with JdkClientHttpConnector [#​29400](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29400)
-   Native image FileSystem should not be closed after classpath scanning [#​29397](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29397)
-   AOT processing loses bean aliases [#​29391](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29391)
-   WebClient and WebFlux Observation do not propagate context [#​29388](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/pull/29388)
-   HttpServiceProxyFactory raises IllegalStateException if created through the builder and declared as a bean [#​29376](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29376)
-   Multiple `@ImportRuntimeHints` in the type hierarchy should be supported [#​29361](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29361)

##### :hammer: Dependency Upgrades

-   Upgrade to Jackson 2.14.0-rc3 [#​29405](https://togithub.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/issues/29405)

[@​fmbenhassine](https://togithub.com/fmbenhassine), [@​imkulwant](https://togithub.com/imkulwant), [@​izeye](https://togithub.com/izeye), and [@​marcingrzejszczak](https://togithub.com/marcingrzejszczak)

</details>
